00:27:26,126 --> 00:27:29,686
MUSIC:
"Last Of The Summer Wine"

361
00:27:46,086 --> 00:27:49,666
'And with the larger orchestra,
the Summer Wine theme

362
00:27:49,666 --> 00:27:53,506
'was given
an extraterrestrial feel.'

363
00:27:53,506 --> 00:27:56,766
Me brakes have gone!
Help!

364
00:28:05,806 --> 00:28:07,926
Ah!
Ohh...

365
00:28:19,926 --> 00:28:22,646
Welcome to Earth!

366
00:28:29,386 --> 00:28:33,606
It makes you wonder
what sort of planet they come from!

367
00:28:33,606 --> 00:28:36,486
Stars appearing in the series

368
00:28:36,486 --> 00:28:39,526
for the odd episode -

369
00:28:39,526 --> 00:28:43,846
very satisfying.
Very pleasurable for me,

370
00:28:43,846 --> 00:28:47,166
in terms of people like Ron Moody.

371
00:28:47,166 --> 00:28:49,806
I wasn't in the business

372
00:28:49,806 --> 00:28:55,086
when I saw Oliver and that
wonderful performance as Fagin.

373
00:28:56,166 --> 00:29:01,166
Then, it's almost the completion
of a little dream

374
00:29:01,166 --> 00:29:06,226
when you see someone like Ron Moody
appearing in a major part,

375
00:29:06,226 --> 00:29:11,266
even if it's only in one episode,
it's very pleasurable.

376
00:29:11,266 --> 00:29:14,026
I have this weak heart.

377
00:29:14,026 --> 00:29:17,226
Weak heart?!

378
00:29:17,226 --> 00:29:20,226
Yes, I'm afraid my life is dated,

379
00:29:20,226 --> 00:29:24,826
circumscribed by the palpitations
of a faulty ticker.

380
00:29:24,826 --> 00:29:30,926
I have the satisfaction
of knowing that I overstrained it
in the service of humanity,

381
00:29:30,926 --> 00:29:35,586
but you can understand why I
couldn't risk hunting for treasure.

382
00:29:35,586 --> 00:29:38,146
I couldn't stand the excitement.

383
00:29:39,766 --> 00:29:42,266
What about the barmaid?

384
00:29:43,946 --> 00:29:46,686
It wasn't like that.

385
00:29:46,686 --> 00:29:50,406
The good woman merely reminded me
of the lady...

386
00:29:50,406 --> 00:29:53,146
who was once my wife.

387
00:30:02,426 --> 00:30:04,426
LOUD SNORT

388
00:30:14,706 --> 00:30:17,226
RESOUNDING CHORDS

389
00:30:38,346 --> 00:30:43,726
When Alan Bell said, "Cut!",
which is the end of the scene,

390
00:30:43,726 --> 00:30:47,786
and he rushed over,
"Are you all right, Norman?"

391
00:30:47,786 --> 00:30:51,946
I looked up at him,
"Yeah, I think... Course I am!"

392
00:30:51,946 --> 00:30:56,026
Sometimes you do hurt yourself,
but I think of the money
and I'm all right!

393
00:30:59,030 --> 00:31:04,730
Just before I started filming,
I picked up a minor ailment
which would stop me filming.

394
00:31:04,730 --> 00:31:08,750
They had to recast
and I suggested Frank Thornton.

395
00:31:08,750 --> 00:31:15,730
I remember Alan Bell was talking
to me on the phone. I was in
the kitchen. I can see it all now.

396
00:31:15,730 --> 00:31:20,570
He said, "It's a great pity about
Brian Wilde having to leave us,

397
00:31:20,570 --> 00:31:24,470
"but we've managed
to get Frank Thornton."

398
00:31:24,470 --> 00:31:27,130
And I said, "Spot on!"

399
00:31:27,130 --> 00:31:29,810
Stay calm! I'm on my way.

400
00:31:30,950 --> 00:31:36,390
If there are any smokers down there,
this is not a good time!

401
00:31:36,390 --> 00:31:40,730
Just stay there!
I'm coming down no-o-ow!

402
00:31:40,730 --> 00:31:42,690
Oops!

403
00:31:44,350 --> 00:31:46,850
Is this yours?!

404
00:31:48,130 --> 00:31:51,950
I was only due
to make about six episodes

405
00:31:51,950 --> 00:31:55,790
as a sort of temporary stand-in
for Brian.

406
00:31:55,790 --> 00:32:00,870
But due to the fragmented nature of
filming - a bit here, a bit there -

407
00:32:00,870 --> 00:32:04,390
and problems
with Brian's availability,

408
00:32:04,390 --> 00:32:09,570
it was impossible for him to come
back and I made all 11 episodes.

409
00:32:09,570 --> 00:32:13,590
Leave this with me.
I can handle policemen.

410
00:32:13,590 --> 00:32:17,210
In two minutes,
they'll be asking for autographs.

411
00:32:21,390 --> 00:32:25,430
Now, then, constables.
It's your lucky day.

412
00:32:25,430 --> 00:32:29,450
How often do you meet
Truly of the Yard?

413
00:32:30,830 --> 00:32:33,650
Thou made a big impression there(!)

414
00:32:33,650 --> 00:32:37,770
They've been up all night.
They're in a bad mood.

415
00:32:37,770 --> 00:32:40,310
I have been invited to go back.

416
00:32:40,310 --> 00:32:45,590
Perhaps one day I will. I'm relieved
not to have to climb those hills!

417
00:32:45,590 --> 00:32:52,870
'In 1999, when we were filming
the millennium special,
we were in France.'

418
00:32:52,870 --> 00:32:56,490
What's this, then?
Your coffee.

419
00:32:56,490 --> 00:32:59,030
I ordered a drink, not a bath!

420
00:32:59,030 --> 00:33:01,570
Where's the basin?

421
00:33:01,570 --> 00:33:06,970
'Bill confided in me that he wasn't
feeling very well.'

422
00:33:06,970 --> 00:33:10,010
And when we got back to England,

423
00:33:10,010 --> 00:33:15,330
I insisted that he get in touch
with a specialist, which he did.

424
00:33:16,510 --> 00:33:21,690
And, sadly, he was diagnosed
to have terminal cancer.

425
00:33:21,690 --> 00:33:25,510
Bill wanted to finish filming.
He wouldn't give up.

426
00:33:25,510 --> 00:33:29,030
We only got him
for the location scenes

427
00:33:29,030 --> 00:33:31,590
shot in Yorkshire.

428
00:33:31,590 --> 00:33:37,710
We then had the problem
of having £1.5 million-worth
of unfinished programming,

429
00:33:37,710 --> 00:33:42,510
so I was forced to take liberties
with the script, put doubles in

430
00:33:42,510 --> 00:33:48,210
and take scenes of Bill that were
shot earlier and electronically
drop them into the finished films.

431
00:33:48,210 --> 00:33:50,990
I think we got away with it.
I don't think anyone noticed.

432
00:33:50,990 --> 00:33:56,210
We were able to see Bill
in his final performance.

